# Best packages in Atom

##### To install any of the packages mentioned in Command Line: "apm install package_name"

### 1) Highlight-Selected

Highlights the current word selected when double clicking

https://atom.io/packages/highlight-selected

### 2) Markdown-image-assistant

Add sane drag and drop and copy/paste support for images to markdown files

https://atom.io/packages/markdown-image-assistant


### 3) PlatformIO IDE Terminal

A terminal package for Atom, complete with themes, API and more for PlatformIO IDE. Fork of terminal-plus.

https://atom.io/packages/platformio-ide-terminal

### 4) Atom Build package

Build your current project, directly from Atom

https://atom.io/packages/build

### 5) Hydrogen

Run code interactively, inspect data, and plot. All the power of Jupyter kernels, inside your favorite text editor.

https://atom.io/packages/hydrogen

### 6) Pigments

A package to display colors in project and files.

https://atom.io/packages/pigments


### 7) Busy Signal

A package that provides an easy to use API to show your package is performing a task

https://atom.io/packages/busy-signal


### 8) Terminal-plus

A terminal package for Atom, complete with themes and more.

https://atom.io/packages/terminal-plus



##  The following are best themes for Atom:



### 9) Atom-material-ui

A dynamic UI theme for Atom that follows Google's Material Design Guidelines

https://atom.io/themes/atom-material-ui

### 10) Atom-material-syntax / Darker

A dark/darker syntax theme for Atom that uses Google's Material Design color palette

- https://atom.io/packages/atom-material-syntax
- https://atom.io/packages/atom-material-syntax-dark
